      <div class="notice">Declaration concerning Personal Information contained within Road video recordings.
 
Data Controller:
The controller is Nissan Motor Ibérica S.A. Zona Franca Sector B, Calle 4 nº 124, CP 08004 Barcelona, Spain, email: data_recording@nissan-europe.com
 
Data Recordings:
Test vehicles operated by Nissan can be fitted with video recording devices, which collect and store images of outside the vehicle during driving on public roads and streets. Those video images may contain personal information such as faces or vehicle number plates. Important to notice is that collection of that data is incidental and not the purpose of the testing. That personal information is not processed or analysed and Nissan is not using as such.
Nissan transfer that data via secure file transfer or upon physical disks from test vehicles to Research&amp;Development offices in Spain, United Kingdom and/or Japan for Advanced Driving Assistance Systems development.
 
Data Retention:
This data will be retained only as long as the development of such systems require or as long as permitted by the applicable laws, whichever is shorter.
 
Individual Rights:
Individuals have the right to request Nissan to delete their personal information from the recordings, provided individuals specify date, time and place the recording took place. Requests can be sent to: data_recording@nissan-europe.com</div>
